The directory `app/Http/Controllers` is intended to contain controller classes. Since you have not specified any particular controller to create, I will provide a basic example of a controller file that you might typically have in this directory.

Here is the content for a sample controller named `ExampleController.php`:

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class ExampleController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        return view('example.index');
    }

    public function show($id)
    {
        return view('example.show', ['id' => $id]);
    }
}